Description:
No annotation on the envelope.

- Reproduction of 'The Israelites Collecting Manna'
- Extracts from different publications
- Journal: "Apollo. Chronique des beaux arts", n. 17, December 1942
- Journal: "De Vlag", n. 8, March 1943 (four copies)
- Article: 'Im Schatten von Rubens. Zum 350. Geburtstag von Jakob Jordaens' in "Brüsseler Zeitung" dated 19.05.1943 (ten copies)
- Article: '"De droomende Sileen" van Peter Pauwel Rubens door dr. Hans Gerhard Evers, professor aan de Universiteit te Munchen' in "Volk en Staat" dated 28.02.1943 (two copies)
- Subfolder:
    - Booklet: "Rubens als Bürger. Rubensausstellung Siegen 1967" (exhibition list)
    - Catalogue: "Siegen '67. Peter Paul Rubens"
- Notes about different paintings (dated 1968)
- Photocopy of a reproduction of 'The Death of Adonis'
- Correspondence with J. O. Leegenhoek (dated 1968), with Margret Köser (dated 1968), with Bernd Roedig (dated 1968), with Manfred Kurtz (dated 1968) and with Klaus Demus (dated 1967)
- Bibliographic references
- Article: 'Un "Rubens" inconnu, découvert à Paris' in "Le Figaro" dated 01.02.1968
- Essay: 'Rubens' Ruf' in "Der Monat", n.233, February 1968
- Business cards of M. Walter Mela and Diethelm Doll
- Essay (reprint): 'Rubens' "Abschied des Adonis" in Düsseldorf' by H. von Einem, in Wallraf-Richartz-Jahrbuch, 1967
- "Consensu-auctoris" letter from Kindlers Malerei-Lexikon with the figures list and the bibliography ("Ad usum auctoris")
- Article: 'Bestandsaufnahme. Karlsruher Gesamtkatalog' in "Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung" dated 21.12.1967
- Photocopy of a 'Madonna with Child'
- Essays: 'Siegen zeigte sich al Kunsrzentrum and Rede des britischen Botschafters, S. E. Sir Frank Roberts anläβlich der Verleihung des Rubenspreises am 28. Juni 1967 in der Bühne der Stadt Siegen' in Siegbild, n.2/67  
  
Loose documentation in the Rubensdocumentation of the Rubenianum:   
     
- Photo of a reproduction of the 'Holy Family' (Rubenianum "Evers 1993" stamp on the back)
